    "updated_at": "2026-01-19T18:07:37Z",
    "body": "If, as Jake said, the problem is a specific class doing something very wrong which should never arise again and will be removed soon - I think it's best we either explicitly treat this ad-hoc in `FromPyObject` (i.e. call `data` for this specific class, in a standalone code that will be easy to remove later) or maybe change `BlueprintCircuit` to avoid the lazy approach, if possible.",
