    "created_at": "2026-01-21T08:23:07Z",
    "updated_at": "2026-01-21T08:23:07Z",
    "body": "`BlueprintCircuit` is subclassed by several classes with each implementing lazy construction in a slightly different way, so removing the lazy approach isn't a worthwhile effort IMO, given they are all pending for removal. Calling `data` in `PyFromObject` isn't so nice for the reasons stated [here](https://github.com/Qiskit/qiskit/pull/14166#discussion_r2702334052).\n\nAdding `_circuit_data` getter to `QuantumCircuit` and overriding it in `BlueprintCircuit` in which it should just call `self._build` seems both minimal and localized, in line with the plan to remove the `BlueprintCircuit` hierarchy soon. Alternatively, I think calling `data()` in QPY dump in case the program is of type `BlueprintCircuit` would also be fine. ",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "pin": null,
