    "updated_at": "2026-01-21T09:08:02Z",
    "body": "Eli: my thing is that I would rather a larger change to every broken class that subclasses `BlueprintCircuit` (they're all deprecated for the same reason) than a minimal change that affects the performance / usability of the actually important `QuantumCircuit`. This is one of the times where I'd go non-minimal, because `QuantumCircuit` is orders of magnitude more important than everything based on `BlueprintCircuit` put together.\n\nThat said, if making QPY aware of `BlueprintCircuit` and forcing a build of it is sufficient to fix all the known bugs, then I'd do that - that's the approach that `BlueprintCircuit` takes everywhere internally.",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
